s%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20US%20after%2025%20years%20in%20the%20UK.%20People%20abroad%20were%20more%20polite%20than%20Americans%2C%20but%20I%20never%20quite%20fit%20in%20there.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20wearing%20a%20hat%20is%20standing%20with%20UK%20nature%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66824fb3c31eb990ea2f9041%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDana%20Mayer%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20US%20after%2025%20years%20in%20the%20UK.%20%3Cp%3EDana%20Mayer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDana%20Mayer%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20US%20after%20living%20in%20the%20UK%20for%2025%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20used%20to%20get%20frustrated%20by%20the%20British%20tendency%20to%20accept%20mediocrity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20she%20cringes%20when%20Americans%20demand%20a%20free%20meal%20because%20their%20drinks%20arrive%20five%20minutes%20late.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20how%20much%20the%20US%20had%20changed%20when%20I%20moved%20back.%20I'd%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-american-misses-after-moving-back-from-uk-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%2025%20years%2C%20but%20when%20the%20pandemic%20kicked%20off%20in%20March%202020%2C%20I%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20go%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20returning%20that%20I%20realized%20how%20British%20I'd%20become%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bhome%26quot%3B%20was%20more%20difficult%20to%20define.%20Now%2C%20after%20having%20lived%20almost%20half%20my%20life%20in%20each%20country%2C%20I%20feel%20equally%20in%20love%20with%20both%2C%20although%20for%20very%20different%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-life-differences-living-in-uk-compared-to-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonal%20space%20in%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20that%20stems%20from%20the%20UK's%20population%20density%20being%20almost%20eight%20times%20that%20of%20the%20US%20per%20square%20mile%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FEN.POP.DNST%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20Open%20Data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20translated%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flondon-dumpster-tiny-home-how-i-use-space-photos-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etiny%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20common%20walls%20even%20in%20the%20countryside%20and%20jostling%20for%20sidewalk%20space%20in%20the%20cities.%20It%20also%20seemed%20to%20result%20in%20a%20populace%20adverse%20to%20talking%20to%20or%20making%20eye%20contact%20with%20strangers%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20their%20perceived%20sanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dbd8a97c-583d-4f3e-8b03-33bfbab9ca06%5C%22%3ESize%20and%20space%20struck%20me%20when%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFresh%20out%20of%20COVID%20quarantine%2C%20I%20was%20visiting%20a%20friend%20in%20a%20New%20York%20City%20suburb%2C%20looking%20around%20their%20giant%20kitchen%20with%20its%20oversized%20fridge.%20I%20didn't%20even%20have%20to%20go%20outside%20to%20their%20huge%20lawn%20or%20the%20wooded%20roads%20surrounding%20the%20property%20to%20feel%20my%20energy%20expand%20into%20what%20was%20simply%20more%20space%20per%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20when%20I%20spotted%20an%20enormous%20orange%20pepper%20on%20the%20kitchen%20counter%20that%20looked%20like%20a%20mutant%20interloper.%20Was%20this%20actually%20food%3F%20Was%20it%20a%20pepper%20crossed%20with%20some%20kind%20of%20alien%20Godzilla%3F%20It%20was%20so%20big%20that%20I%20took%20a%20picture.%20I%20s