ound-dead-in-madhya-pradesh-house-probe-on-6010947%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fcities%2Fmadhya-pradesh-alirajpur-farmer-wife-and-3-children-found-dead-in-madhya-pradesh-house-probe-on-6010947%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian-American%20Man's%20Rs%208%2C300%20Crore%20Fraud%20Scheme%20Shakes%20Top%20US%20Investors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20Indian-American%20businessman%20Rishi%20Shah%2C%20the%20former%20billionaire%20cofounder%20of%20Outcome%20Health%2C%20has%20been%20sentenced%20to%20seven%20and%20a%20half%20years%20in%20prison%20by%20a%20US%20court.%20The%20saga%20involves%20a%20Rs%208%2C300%20crore%20(%241%20billion)%20fraud%20scheme%20that%20shook%20high-profile%20investors%20like%20Goldman%20Sachs%20Group%20Inc.%2C%20Google%20parent%20Alphabet%20Inc.%2C%20and%20Illinois%20Governor%20JB%20Pritzker's%20venture%20capital%20firm.%20The%20verdict%2C%20handed%20down%20by%20US%20District%20Judge%20Thomas%20Durkin%2C%20closed%20the%20lid%20on%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20corporate%20fraud%20cases%20in%20recent%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Bloomberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fprivate-equity%2Fex-billionaire-gets-7-1-2-years-for-defrauding-goldman-google%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Outcome%20Health%20was%20a%20brainchild%20of%20Mr%20Shah%20during%20his%20university%20days.%20Originally%20known%20as%20Context%20Media%20Health%2C%20the%20company%20was%20founded%20in%202006%20with%20a%20vision%20of%20changing%20medical%20advertising%20through%20installing%20televisions%20at%20doctors'%20offices%20to%20stream%20health%20ads%20targeted%20at%20patients.%20Mr%20Shah%20was%20joined%20by%20his%20co-founder%20Shradha%20Agrawal%2C%20and%20the%20growth%20for%20the%20company%20became%20exponential%20as%20far%20as%20valuation%20was%20concerned%2C%20all%20in%20the%20quest%20to%20bridge%20the%20communication%20gap%20between%20patients%20and%20healthcare%20providers%20innovatively%20through%20ad%20placements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20mid-2010s%2C%20Outcome%20Health%20had%20emerged%20as%20a%20big%20player%20in%20the%20tech%20and%20healthcare%20investment%20communities.%20The%20promise%20of%20meshing%20cutting-edge%20technology%20into%20traditional%20healthcare%20marketing%20beckoned%20high-profile%20investors.%20During%20its%20meteoric%20rise%2C%20Outcome%20was%20securing%20enormous%20funds%20and%20clientele%2C%20placing%20Mr%20Shah%20as%20a%20rising%20star%20in%20Chicago%20corporate%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELies%20And%20Deceit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20behind%20the%20glittering%20success%2C%20Outcome%20Health's%20foundations%20were%20rotting.%20Prosecutors%20said%20Mr%20Shah%2C%2038%2C%20along%20with%20Ms%20Agarwal%20and%20another%20defendant%2C%20chief%20financial%20officer%20Brad%20Purdy%2C%20engaged%20in%20a%20scheme%20of%20monumental%20fraud%20against%20investors%2C%20clients%2C%20and%20lenders%20by%20misrepresenting%20the%20operational%20and%20financial%20health%20of%20the%20company.%20At%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20fraud%20was%20selling%20more%20advertising%20inventory%20than%20could%20be%20delivered%20by%20Outcome%20Health%2C%20and%20fabricating%20data%20to%20cover%20up%20the%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20defrauded%20pharmaceutical%20giant%20Novo%20Nordisk%20A%2FS%20and%20other%20clients%20about%20its%20network%20size%20and%20ad%20reach.%20Misleading%20information%2C%20combined%20with%20fraudulent%20data%2C%20painted%20a%20picture%20of%20exponential%20revenue%20growth%20that%20beguiled%20further%20investment%20or%20financial%20backing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Shah%20lived%20life%20to%20the%20fullest%20because%20the%20money%20rolling%20in%20from%20the%20inflated%20ad%20sales%20and%20financing%20from%20investors%20was%20huge.%20Reports%20exposed%20this%20spending%20habit%2C%20featuring%20exotic%20trips%20with%20private%20jets%20and%20yachts%2C%20even%20the%20purchase%20of%20a%20%2410%20million%20home.%20In%202016%2C%20Mr%20Shah's%20net%20worth%20was%20pegged%20at%20more%20than%20%244%20billion%2C%20reflecting%20an%20amount%20depreciated%20and%20inflated%20by%20a%20raft%20of%20duplicitous%20accounting%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20facade%20began%20to%20crumble%20in%202017%20when%20a%20media%20expose%20by%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20brought%20the%20fraudulent%20activities%20into%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20a%20group%20of%20investors%20that%20included%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20Alphabet%2C%20and%20Governor%20Pritzker's%20firm%20filed%20lawsuits%20against%20Outcome%20Health%2C%20accusing%20the%20firm%20of%20fraud%20in%20its%20%24487.5%20million%20fundraising%20earlier%20in%20the%20year.%20The%20fundraiser%20had%20returned%20a%20%24225%20million%20dividend%20for%20Mr%20Shah%20and%20Ms%20Agarwal%20but%20left%20investors%20holding%20a%20grossly%20overvalued%20stake%20in%20a%20company%20teetering%20on%20collapse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Consequences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Shah%20was%20indicted%20on%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20counts%20of%20fraud%20and%20money%20laundering%20until%20he%20was%20convicted%20on%20these%20charges%20in%20April%202023.%20He%20was%20joined%20by%20Ms%20Agarwal%20and%20Mr%20Purdy.%20While%20the%20prosecutors%20asked%20for%2015%20years%20for%20Mr%20Shah%20and%2010%20years%20for%20his%20co-conspirators%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDistrict%20Judge%20Durkin's%20final%20rulings%20were%20disparate%20and%20included%20a%20three-year%20sentence%20for%20Ms%20Agarwal%20in%20a%20halfway%20house%20and%20Mr%20Purdy%20two%20years%20and%20three%20months%20in%20prison.%20Aside%20from%20the%20criminal%20case%2C%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20of%20the%20US%20has%20likewise%20filed%20a%20civil%20action%20against%20Mr%20Shah%2C%20Ms%20Agarwal%2C%20Mr%20Purdy%2C%20and%20former%20chief%20growth%20officer%20Ashik%20Desai.%20Mr%20Desai%20and%20other%20Outcome%20employees%20had%20pleaded%20guilty%20already%20before%20the%20jury%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20Apology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Shah%2C%20in%20ill%20health%2C%20spoke%20of%20remorse%20and%20accepted%20responsibility%20at%20sentencing.%20In%20a%20prepared%20remark%20he%20accepted%20his%20failure%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20management%20of%20the%20aggressive%20Outcome%20Health%20expansion%20and%20creating%20a%20corporate%20culture%20that%20led%20through%20deceptive%20practices.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bashamed%20and%20embarrassed%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20misconduct%20that%20brought%20down%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20culture%20I%20created%20permissioned%20people%20on%20my%20team%20to%20think%20it%20was%20okay%20to%20create%20false%20data%20in%20response%20to%20a%20client%20question.%26quot%3B%20he%20confessed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719885900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Ffhb2falg_rishi-shah-_625x300_02_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Findian-american-man-rishi-shahs-rs-8-300-crore-fraud-scheme-shakes-top-us-investors-6014486%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Indian-American%20businessman%20Rishi%20Shah%2C%20the%20former%20billionaire%20cofounder%20of%20Outcome%20Health%2C%20has%20been%20sentenced%20to%20seven%20and%20a%20half%20years%20in%20prison%20by%20a%20US%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Findian-american-man-rishi-shahs-rs-8-300-crore-fraud-scheme-shakes-top-us-investors-6014486%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Findian-american-man-rishi-shahs-rs-8-300-crore-fraud-scheme-shakes-top-us-investors-6014486%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Findian-american-man-rishi-shahs-rs-8-300-crore-fraud-sc