Patrick%20Rush%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20financial%20planner%20who%20works%20with%20millionaire%20clients%20says%20many%20have%20similar%20habits%20that%20keep%20them%20wealthy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHis%20richest%20clients%20have%20a%20financial%20plan%20and%20stick%20to%20it%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20try%20to%20time%20the%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20also%20tend%20to%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20reduce%20their%20taxes%2C%20and%20over-plan%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20wealthy%20people%20have%20ways%20of%20making%20their%20money%20last.%20And%2C%20after%20years%20of%20advising%20high%20net%20worth%20people%2C%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftriadfa.com%2Fteam-member%2Fpatrick-rush-cfp-cap-clu-mba%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatrick%20Rush%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20many%20of%20his%20clients%20have%20a%20few%20traits%20in%20common.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20our%20clients%20are%20the%20millionaire%20next%20door%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20weren't%20huge%20income%20earners%2C%20but%20just%20really%20disciplined%20savers%2C%20socking%20money%20away%20into%20401(k)s%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20accumulated%20over%20%241%20million%20when%20they're%20ready%20to%20retire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20years%20of%20experience%20working%20with%20such%20people%2C%20he%20says%20there%20are%20five%20approaches%20he%20commonly%20sees%20that%20help%20wealthy%20people%20keep%20growing%20their%20money%20over%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Wealthy%20people%20have%20a%20financial%20plan%20and%20stick%20to%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWealthy%20people%20who%20keep%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20build%20%E2%80%94%20their%20wealth%20over%20time%20always%20have%20a%20bigger-picture%20financial%20plan%2C%20Rush%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20of%20his%20millionaire%20clients%2C%20a%20financial%20plan%20doesn't%20just%20refer%20to%20how%20they'll%20spend%20and%20save.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20know%20all%20the%20nuts%20and%20bolts%20about%20a%20family's%20budgeting%20and%20expenses%2C%20what%20kind%20of%20insurance%20they%20have%2C%20what%20their%20estate%20planning%20looks%20like%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20legal%20documents%2C%20and%20their%20goals%20for%20potentially%20leaving%20a%20legacy%20behind%20for%20either%20family%20members%20or%20charitable%20organizations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Oftentimes%2C%20financial%20planning%20also%20considers%20taxes%2C%20employer%20benefits%2C%20and%20investing%20plans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWealthy%20people%20get%20the%20right%20help%20with%20making%20this%20plan%20and%20know%20what%20steps%20they%20have%20to%20take%20today%20to%20stick%20to%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20They're%20neither%20worried%20about%20their%20investments%20nor%20managing%20them%20often%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20wealthy%20people%20Rush%20works%20with%20don't%20have%20stock%20trading%20on%20their%20minds.%20They're%20not%20thinking%20about%20trying%20to%20time%20the%20market%20or%20making%20lots%20of%20cash%20on%20the%20next%20hot%20stock.%20Instead%2C%20Rush%20says%20he%20encourages%20clients%20to%20take%20a%20long%20view%20of%20investing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20try%20to%20outwit%20the%20markets.%20We%20just%20want%20to%20harness%20the%20power%20of%20the%20markets%20to%20give%20our%20investors%20the%20highest%20probability%20of%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20Business%20Insider.%20Oftentimes%2C%20simply%20buying%20shares%20and%20holding%20onto%20them%20for%20the%20long%20term%20creates%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20of%20Rush's%20wealthy%20clients%2C%20investing%20isn't%20an%20active%20process%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20about%20patience.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20right%20every%20year%2C%20or%20every%20three%20years%2C%20or%20even%20every%20five%20years.%20But%2C%20we%20know%20that%20over%20time%2C%20we%20are%20giving%20our%20clients%20the%20highest%20probability%20of%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20They've%20over-planned%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20people%2C%20retiring%20from%20full-time%20work%20means%20living%20on%20a%20smaller%20income%20and%20making%20sacrifices.%20But%2C%20wealthy%20people%20stay%20wealthy%20in%20retirement%20with%20some%20careful%20planning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERush%20says%20that%20his%20clients%20often%20over-plan%20for%20retirement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20use%20the%20life%20expectancy%20of%20age%2096%20for%20our%20clients%2C%20because%20we%20know%20there's%20about%20a%2025%25%20chance%20that%20for%20a%20healthy%2065-year-old%20couple%2C%20at%20least%20one%20of%20them%20will%20live%20to%20age%2096.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20over-planning%2C%20wealthy%20people%20are%20able%20to%20maintain%20the%20same%20standard%20of%20living%20in%20retirement%20for%20longer.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20we%20want%20is%20for%20you%20to%20run%20out%20of%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20They%20find%20ways%20to%20reduce%20their%20taxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20careful%20planning%2C%20wealthy%20people%20have%20learned%20to%20reduce%20how%20much%20they%20owe%20in%20taxes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20know%20how%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20certain%20tax%20breaks%20and%20incentives%20and%20decrease%20the%20amount%20of%20taxes%20they%20owe%20both%20now%20and%20later%20in%20retirement.%20While%20taxes%20can%20be%20a%20complicated%20thing%20to%20understand%2C%20reducing%20taxes%20is%20part%20of%20their%20overall%20financial%20plan%2C%20and%20it's%20considered%20at%20every%20step%2C%20from%20where%20they%20invest%20to%20how%20they%20give%20gifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaying%20less%20in%20taxes%20means%20keeping%20more%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20For%20people%20who%20have%20grown%20their%20wealth%20and%20slowly%20moved%20into%20higher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-tax-bracket-am-i-in%5C%22%3Etax%20brackets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reducing%20their%20total%20taxes%20is%20a%20critical%20way%20to%C2%A0maintain%20their%20wealth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20They%20incorporate%20charitable%20giving%20into%20their%20financial%20planning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHand%20in%20hand%20with%20tax%20efficiency%2C%20wealthy%20people%20often%20include%20charitable%20giving%20in%20their%20financial%20plans.%20Not%20only%20do%20most%20wealthy%20people%20feel%20an%20obligation%20to%20give%20back%2C%20but%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20tax%20advantages%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20gifts%20could%20come%20in%20a%20number%20of%20forms%2C%20Rush%20says.%20They%20could%20be%20monetary%20donations%2C%20but%20they%20could%20also%20be%20gifts%20of%20shares%20of%20stock%2C%20or%20distributions%20from%20an%20IRA%20after%20a%20certain%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharitable%20contributions%20can%20help%20lower%20the%20total%20taxable%20income%2C%20which%20could%20in%20turn%20reduce%20income%20taxes%20and%20even%20Medicare%20premiums%20in%20retirement.%20Donating%20has%20two%20purposes%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20beneficial%20in%20more%20ways%20than%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20January%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-planner-rich-people-stay-wealthy-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719870722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6011c86d6dfbe10018e0054e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-planner-rich-people-stay-wealthy-202