%26quot%3BWith%20the%20January%206th%20case%2C%20the%20one%20that%20was%20at%20issue%20here%2C%20this%20makes%20it%20absolutely%20clear%20there's%20no%20way%20this%20is%20going%20to%20trial%20before%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cliff%20Sloan%2C%20a%20Georgetown%20University%20law%20professor%20and%20constitutional%20law%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20Florida%20case%2C%20the%20decision%20has%20no%20direct%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20Michel%20Paradis%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20teaches%20national%20security%20and%20constitutional%20law%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20disrupt%20and%20complicate%20the%20prosecution%2C%20in%20so%20far%20as%20there%20will%20be%20a%20new%20round%20of%20arguments%20on%20how%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20affects%20the%20transportation%20of%20documents%2C%20etc.%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESloan%20said%20that%20it's%20possible%20that%20Trump's%20attorneys%20make%20new%20arguments%20in%20the%20classified%20documents%20case%20based%20on%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%2C%20but%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3BIt'll%20be%20more%20difficult%20because%20the%20core%20of%20that%20case%20has%20to%20do%20with%20actions%20he%20took%20when%20he%20was%20no%20longer%20president%20with%20regard%20to%20classified%20documents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Trump%20can%20now%20argue%20that%20before%20he%20left%20office%2C%20he%20somehow%20%26quot%3Bdeclassified%26quot%3B%20the%20documents%2C%20an%20official%20act%20that%20now%20cannot%20be%20challenged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20say%20Trump%20broke%20federal%20law%20when%20he%20took%20documents%20with%20him%20from%20the%20White%20House%20to%20Mar-a-Lago%2C%20his%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20Florida%2C%20estate%20and%20private%20club.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Florida%20litigation%20will%20be%20all%20the%20more%20complicated%2C%20Paradis%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20held%20that%20you%20can't%20inquire%20into%20a%20president's%20'motives'%20for%20taking%20any%20official%20act.%20And%20so%20precisely%20how%20that%20will%20work%20is%20up%20in%20the%20air%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Monday's%20decision%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20dividing%20official%20from%20unofficial%20conduct%2C%20courts%20may%20not%20inquire%20into%20the%20president's%20motives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BSuch%20a%20'highly%20intrusive%20inquiry%20would%20risk%20exposing%20even%20the%20most%20obvious%20instances%20of%20official%20conduct%20to%20judicial%20examination%20on%20the%20mere%20allegation%20of%20improper%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECircling%20back%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-read-charges-january-6-election-case-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJanuary%206%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20that%20indictment's%20allegations%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20now%20be%20challenged%20as%20an%20official%20act%20for%20which%20he%20is%20immune%20from%20prosecution%2C%20said%20Paradis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20pressure%20his%20acting%20attorney%20general%20and%20the%20Justice%20Department%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%20results.%20Those%20discussions%20%26quot%3Bare%20readily%20categorized%26quot%3B%20as%20official%20acts%2C%20Monday's%20decision%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20true%20even%20if%20Smith's%20claims%20are%20correct%2C%20and%20Trump's%20efforts%20were%20improper%2C%20the%20decision%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20President%20cannot%20be%20prosecuted%20for%20conduct%20within%20his%20exclusive%20constitutional%20authority%2C%20Trump%20is%20absolutely%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20for%20the%20alleged%20conduct%20involving%20his%20discussions%20with%20Justice%20Department%20officials%2C%20the%20decision%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOther%20allegations%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20those%20involving%20Trump's%20interactions%20with%20the%20vice%20president%2C%20state%20officials%2C%20and%20certain%20private%20parties%2C%20and%20his%20comments%20to%20the%20general%20public%20%E2%80%94%20present%20more%20difficult%20questions%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20now%20be%20argued%20over%2C%20the%20decision%20also%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20difficulty%20will%20be%20proving%20that%20something%20is%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20official%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20Paradis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20set%20up%20the%20new%20rule%20is%20that%20most%20everything%20the%20president%20does%20is%20'presumptively%20immune%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20then%20falls%20to%20the%20prosecution%20to%20show%20that%20the%20'presumptively'%20official%20act%20was%20in%20fact%20'unofficial.'%20However%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20is%20where%20Justice%20Barrett%20broke%20with%20the%20majority%20%E2%80%94%20prosecutors%20can't%20inquire%20into%20the%20president's%20motives%20and%20are%20also%20largely%20prohibited%20from%20inquiring%20into%20the%20president's%20communications%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20you%20have%20to%20show%20what%20the%20president%20intended%20while%20being%20forbidden%20from%20proving%20what%20was%20in%20his%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20Paradis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20that%20new%20measure%2C%20any%20communication%20Trump%20has%20with%20another%20federal%20official%20is%2C%20for%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20immune%20from%20prosecution%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20decision%2C%20Sloan%20said%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20%26quot%3Bunwilling%20to%20say%20that%20even%20a%20single%20allegation%20in%20the%20indictment%26quot%3B%20against%20Trump%20over%20his%20over%20his%20efforts%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-read-charges-january-6-election-case-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoverturn%20the%202020%20election%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bwas%20an%20example%20of%20an%20unofficial%20act.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20willing%20to%20say%20some%20things%20were%20clearly%20official%20acts%2C%20but%20it%20was%20unwilling%20to%20give%20a%20single%20example%20of%20something%20that%20was%20unofficial%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sloan%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BCourts%20would%20have%20to%20sort%20out%20what's%20official%20and%20what's%20unofficial%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20official%2C%20what%20kind%20of%20official%20action%20is%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20everything%20else%2C%20it's%20a%20kind%20of%20complicated%20structure%2C%20is%20very%20unpredictable%2C%20and%20it%20just%20puts%20it%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20courts%20to%20make%20these%20judgments%2C%26quot%3B%20Sloan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-smith-donald-trump-presidential-immunity-prosecutions-survive-scotus-barely-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719868599000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668322a51f0c1cd6d7307f36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-smith-donald-trump-presidential-immunity-prosecutions-survive-scotus-barely-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Both%20of%20Jack%20Smith's%20prosecutions%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20could%20be%20delayed%20and%20diminished%20by%20Monday's%20Supreme%20Court's%20immunity%20decision%2C%20experts%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22litaliano%40insider.com%20(Laura%20Italiano%2CNatalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A69%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-smith-donald-trump-presidential-immunity-prosecutions-survive-scotus-barely-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%2